url: "https://github.com/wmarcelod/ecu_simulator"
repository-code: "https://github.com/wmarcelod/ecu_simulator/tree/feat/uds-isotp-bootloader-merged"
license: CC-BY-4.0
keywords:
  - automotive cybersecurity
  - CAN bus
  - UDS
  - ISO 14229
  - ISO 15765-2
  - ECU bootloader
  - firmware extraction
  - testbed
  - intrusion detection
abstract: >-
  Reproducible CAN bus traces and synthetic firmware images produced by the
  ECU-HybridLab testbed reproducing the UDS-based bootloader-extraction
  kill-chain documented in the master's dissertation case study.  Initially
  observed in Ford instrument clusters and replicated in a Volkswagen T-Cross
  in field conditions, the chain follows: bus conditioning → 0x10 DSC →
  0x11 ECU Reset → bootloader entry → 0x27 SecurityAccess seed/key → 0x23
  ReadMemoryByAddress segmented dump.
